  "prompt": "How much is expected cut off for HRM programme for TISSNET 2017?",
  "response": "The Tata Institute of Social Sciences (TISS) conducts the TISS National Entrance Test (TISSNET) for admission into various programs, including the Human Resource Management (HRM) program. The cutoff for the HRM program at TISS can vary each year based on several factors such as the number of applicants, the difficulty level of the exam, and the performance of the candidates.\n\nFor TISSNET 2017, the cutoff for the HRM program was around 75-80 marks out of 100. However, please note that this is an approximate range and the actual cutoff may have varied slightly.\n\nTo give you a better idea, here are the approximate cutoffs for the HRM program at TISS for the past few years:\n\n- TISSNET 2017: 75-80 marks\n- TISSNET 2018: 78-82 marks\n- TISSNET 2019: 80-84 marks\n- TISSNET 2020: 77-81 marks\n\nKeep in mind that these are approximate figures and the actual cutoffs may have been different. It's always a good idea to aim higher than the expected cutoff to increase your chances of getting admission into the HRM program at TISS.\n\nIf you have any more questions or need further information, feel free to ask!",
